\i\b\fs28 \cf0 16. Arsenal
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f0 \cf0 This empty room contains empty weapons racks, along with the usual dust and cobwebs. Three dwarves lies dead in this room. Their corpses are stony, like those seen elsewhere.
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

\i\b\fs28 \cf0 17. Training Room
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f0 \cf0 Thulian soldiers trained in this room. It contains nine mechanical apparatuses that each hold a sword and shield. On the western wall is a control panel with a series of 10 switches. If a character activates one of the switches, roll a die. A roll of 1 through 9 activates apparatuses equal to the result. They move about the room on grooves on the floor, swinging their swords. A result of 10 shuts down any active apparatuses.
\f1 \

\f0 The apparatuses are not intelligent and cannot leave the grooves, which run north to south, with three per row. They have AC 8 and deal 1\'966 points of damage per successful hit, striking as 1 HD creatures. While even one apparatus is in operation, the door locks and does not open again, except by magic or picking the lock.
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

\i\b\fs28 \cf0 18. Laboratory
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f0 \cf0 This room was once a laboratory of some sort. There is a long, metal-reinforced wooden table here, covered in stains in a variety of colors. Along the walls are many metallic shelves, some of which are also stained. Strewn about the room are shards of glass. There is also evidence of other wooden furniture having once been here, but it is now reduced to rotten splinters. 
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

\i\b\fs28 \cf0 19. Archive
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f0 \cf0 This chamber once held a small library of scrolls and codices of a military or historical nature. Now, the metal shelves that line the walls are sparse. The remaining texts are completely valueless and/or crumble to dust if a character touches them. The exceptions are the following:
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f2 \cf0 \'81\'45
\f3 	
\f0 An annotated copy of 
\i Arto Bellumoi
\i0 , a text on strategy and tactics. If a fighting man reads it over the course of one week, it grants 500 experience points (usable once).
\f1 \

\f2 \'81\'45
\f3 	
\f0 An old map of a place called \'93the exarchate of Theana\'94 that would be worth about 500 gp to an interested buyer.
\f1 \

\f2 \'81\'45
\f3 	
\f0  A burnt 
\i scroll of ward against magic
\i0 . If read, there is a 50% chance of its removing one spell of the lowest level known from the mind of the caster rather than working as intended.
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

