\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

\i\b\fs28 \cf0 21. Workshop
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f0 \cf0 This room contains a large metal table and lots of metal shelves. Along the south wall are three unusual metal \'93boxes\'94 festooned with knobs and dials. The boxes are hollow and stand a little over four feet tall. They are warm to the touch. The floor immediately around them is charred and stained with silvery, metallic splotches. Anyone who fiddles with the knobs and dials causes a box to activate with a loud whirring sound that lasts for 1\'964 rounds. Roll for wandering monsters each round it is active. An activated box shoots out a jet of steam that deals 1\'9610 damage to anyone standing immediately in front of the box. A successful saving throw versus dragon breath reduces the damage by half.
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

\i\b\fs28 \cf0 22. Oil Trap
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sa120

\f0 \cf0 This large room is bereft of any furnishings. There are marks on the floor and walls indicating that there were such things in the room at one time in the past. The room is not dusty nor is there much in the way of debris here. The floor of the eastern two-thirds of the room has been coated with a thick layer of oil that is visible if a character gets within 10 feet of it. The oil is flammable and is part of the kobolds' defense of their caverns (see Room 23).
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab709\sb240\sa120

